.TH OB3ECT 1 "2026-05-17" "ob3ect" "Imscribing Grammar"
.SH NAME
ob3ect \- generate and verify self-imscribing categorical programs
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B python auto.py
.I DESCRIPTION
.RB [ \-\-domain
.IR DOMAIN ]
.RB [ \-\-scope
.IR SCOPE ]
.RB [ \-\-provider
.IR PROVIDER ]
.RB [ \-\-model
.IR MODEL ]
.RB [ \-\-retries
.IR N ]
.RB [ \-\-temp
.IR T ]
.PP
.B python digital/runall.py
.PP
.B python digital/frob.py
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ob3ect
is a pipeline for designing, generating, and verifying
.I self-imscribing categorical programs
\(em programs that verify their own algebraic closure.
.PP
An ob3ect is formally a
.I special Frobenius algebra
(A,\ \[*m],\ \[*d],\ \[*h],\ \[*e])
in the monoidal category
.B Prog/~
of programs modulo semantic equivalence, satisfying the
.I special condition:
.PP
.RS
\[*m] \(co \[*d] = id_A
.RE
.PP
In concrete terms:
.B ast.unparse(ast.parse(src))
must be structurally equivalent to
.B src
under
.BR ast.compare() .
This is the discriminating gate.
Every ob3ect in the digital tower passes before it is committed.
.PP
The primary interface is
.BR auto.py ,
which accepts a natural-language description and drives an LLM through the
eight-phase IMASM pipeline, verifying the Frobenius condition at phase 2.
On failure the pipeline retries with a targeted correction prompt.
On pass it writes
.I digital/<slug>/<slug>_ob3ect.py
and prints the artifact report.
.PP
.B digital/runall.py
executes the full 14-layer categorical tower.
Each layer reports
.I Closure: True
or fails loudly.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.I DESCRIPTION
Natural-language description of the ob3ect to generate.
Multi-word; quote the whole description.
This is the only required argument.
.TP
.BR \-\-domain " " \fIDOMAIN\fR
Domain type hint passed to the LLM.
Shapes the vocabulary used in opcode mapping.
Values:
.BR computational ,
.BR biological ,
.BR physical ,
.BR social ,
.BR alchemical ,
.BR oneiric ,
or any free-form string.
Default:
.BR computational .
.TP
.BR \-\-scope " " \fISCOPE\fR
Generation scope.
Controls how broadly the LLM reasons about context and dependencies.
Values:
.BR local ,
.BR mesoscale ,
.BR maximal .
Default:
.BR local .
.TP
.BR \-\-provider " " \fIPROVIDER\fR
LLM provider override.
Values:
.BR openrouter ,
.BR deepseek ,
.BR local .
Default: local fine-tuned Qwen3 endpoint.
.TP
.BR \-\-model " " \fIMODEL\fR
Model ID passed to the provider.
Examples:
.BR qwen/qwen3-235b-a22b ,
.BR deepseek-chat .
.TP
.BR \-\-retries " " \fIN\fR
Maximum number of Frobenius correction retries on FAIL.
Default: 3.
.TP
.BR \-\-temp " " \fIT\fR
LLM temperature (float).
Default: provider default (typically 0.7).
.SH THE IMASM INSTRUCTION SET
Every ob3ect maps all 12 IMASM opcodes.
Unmapped opcodes cause phase 1 to fail.
.TS
tab(|) allbox;
lb lb lb
l l l.
Family|Opcode|Role
Logical|VINIT|Initial object \(em void / pre-imscription state
Logical|TANCH|Terminal anchor \(em closed, verified boundary
Logical|AFWD|Forward morphism (construction / elaboration)
Logical|AREV|Contravariant (descent / deconstruction)
Logical|CLINK|Composition \(co (sequential chaining)
Logical|IMSCRIB|Identity id \(em self-reference
Frobenius|FSPLIT|Comultiplication \[*d]: A\(->A@A (branching / parsing)
Frobenius|FFUSE|Multiplication \[*m]: A@A\(->A (reconstitution / unparsing)
Dialetheia|EVALT|True lattice \(em affirmative branch
Dialetheia|EVALF|False lattice \(em error / negative branch
Dialetheia|ENGAGR|Both \(em dialetheia held without resolution
Linear|IFIX|ROM fixation \(em permanent, irreversible commitment
.TE
.PP
The bootstrap sequence is fixed across all IMASM systems:
.PP
.RS
.B IMSCRIB \(-> AREV \(-> FSPLIT \(-> AFWD \(-> FFUSE \(-> CLINK \(-> IFIX \(-> IMSCRIB
.RE
.PP
The final opcode is
.B IMSCRIB
\(em the loop re-imscribes itself.
.SH PIPELINE PHASES
.TS
tab(|) allbox;
lb lb lb lb
l l l l.
Phase|Name|Artifact|Gate
0|Boundary Define|Domain Charter|Scope + 3+ tokens required
1|Primitive Scan|Opcode Map (12\(mu2)|All 12 opcodes mapped
2|Frobenius Verify|Split/Fuse Report|\[*m]\(co\[*d] = id must PASS
3|Register Map|State Transition Table|All 4 states defined
4|Bootstrap Design|8-Step Sequence|Closure verified
5|exOS Spec|Runtime Environment|All kernel services present
6|Entropy Audit|\[*D]S Report|\[*D]S \(ap 0
7|Instantiate|Ob3ect Artifact|All phases complete
.TE
.PP
Phase 2 is the discriminating gate.
Most designed systems fail
.I \[*m]\(co\[*d] = id
on the first pass because they have irreversible branching they did not account for.
The automated pipeline retries with a targeted correction prompt until PASS
or
.B --retries
is exhausted.
.SH THE DIGITAL TOWER
The tower is in
.I digital/
and is executed by
.BR digital/runall.py .
14 layers, each self-verifying.
.TS
tab(|) allbox;
lb lb
l l.
Layer|Mathematical structure
Category|Small category on AST node types; identity + associativity
Frobenius|Special Frobenius algebra; \[*m]\(co\[*d] = id
Hopf|Frobenius + antipode S; S\(coS = id, S anti-homomorphism
Monad|Triple (T, \[*h], \[*m]); left unit, right unit, associativity
Topos|CCC + subobject classifier; power objects
CCC|Cartesian closed; products \(mu exponentials
Quantum|Superposition over AST branches; measurement collapses to identity
Linear Logic|!-free resource accounting; no cloning, no weakening
IVM|Imscription VM; traced monoidal; handles shared-name programs
HoTT|Higher paths; univalence: equivalent types are identical
Imscription OS|Autopoietic kernel; 10 self-imscribing processes
ProofBridge|Bridge to Lean 4 formal proofs in proofs/
String Diagrams|Graphical calculus; snake / spider / monad wire rewriting
Auto-Imscriber|Meta-layer; generates new ob3ects into digital/test/
.TE
