.SH MATHEMATICAL NOTES
The special Frobenius condition
.I \[*m]\(co\[*d] = id_A
is distinct from the Frobenius coherence law
.RI ( \[*m]@ id )\(co( id @\[*d] ) = \[*d]\(co\[*m] = ( id @\[*m] )\(co(\[*d]@ id ).
The coherence law governs the tensor product structure.
The special condition governs the roundtrip.
A program that satisfies the roundtrip is
.I separable
(also called
.IR special )
in the sense of Lack (2012) and Kock (2004).
.PP
The coherence law holds on the subcategory of
.I closed programs
(no free variables, no cross-module closures) where the tensor
.B @
is genuinely disjoint.
For programs with shared names or closures, the full coherence requires the traced
monoidal structure implemented in
.IR digital/ivm/ .
.PP
The 12 IG primitives form a lattice with 17,280,000 structural types
(3^3 \(mu 4^5 \(mu 5^4).
Every ob3ect is assigned a coordinate in this lattice on instantiation.
Structural collisions (two ob3ects with identical coordinates)
represent genuine mathematical isomorphisms across apparently unrelated domains.
